1. What is your day-to-day activities and what is the process and what is the role and responsibilities? So how you worked on it?

In my day-to-day work activities, 
I mainly focus on developing and maintaining applications using Power Apps, Power Automate, SharePoint, and Dataverse. 
I usually start my day by checking my assigned tasks and attending the daily Srcum meeting where I discuss my progress and any blockers. 
Based on the requirements given by the business users, I analyze the requirement, design the data structure, and decide whether to use SharePoint or Dataverse. 
Then I develop the Power App, connect it to the data source, and implement the business logic using formulas and conditions.

I also create Power Automate flows to automate processes like approval workflows, email notifications, and updating data automatically. 
After development, I test the application, fix any issues, and support the UAT process with business users. 
Once everything is approved, I deploy the solution to production. 

Apart from development, I also handle bug fixes, performance improvements, and enhancements based on user feedback. 
Overall, my role involves end-to-end development, automation, deployment, and support of Power Platform solutions.
At the end of day, I update task status in Azure Board and push my changes for review.
